===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|yfel|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*ubilaz}} (compare Saterland Frisian {{term|eeuwel|lang=stq}}, Dutch {{term|euvel|lang=nl}}, Low German {{term|Övel|lang=nds}}, German {{term|übel|lang=de}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*h₂upélos}}, diminutive of {{m|ine-pro|*h₂wep-|*h₂wep-, *h₂wap-|treat badly}} (compare {{etyl|hit|-}} ''huwappi'' 'to mistreat, harass', ''huwappa'' 'evil, badness').{{rfscript|und|sc=Xsux}}, or alternatively from {{m|ine-pro|*upélos||evil|lit=going over or beyond (acceptable limits)}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*upo}}, {{m|ine-pro|*up}}, {{m|ine-pro|*eup||down, up, over}}.

